content:
Insurance uses managed and unmanaged packages that you install in a certain order. The number of packages you install depends on which features you plan to use.

Basic Package Installation Flow

You install at least three packages to use Insurance:

1. The Insurance and Vlocity Health Managed Package.
2. The Insurance and Vlocity Health Unmanaged Package.
3. The Vlocity Installation Assistant.

Package Installation Flow with the Insurance Industries Extension Packages

To use all of the great features in our Insurance Industries Extension packages, you must have the required licenses. Install the packages in this order:

1. The Insurance and Vlocity Health Managed Package.
2. This package contains data model extensions, Apex Insurance services, templates, cards, Lightning components, product modeling components, and rating engine components.
3. The Insurance Industries Extension Managed Package.
4. If you have the add-on licenses for Policy Administration and Claims Management, enable these features before installing this package.
5. The Vlocity Insurance and Vlocity Health Unmanaged Package.
6. This package contains the Lightning record pages for product modeling and rating UIs, as well as UIs for quotes, policies, and other objects.
7. The Insurance FSC Unmanaged Package.
8. If you decide to install this package, enable Digital Experience Sites first.

Install Managed Packages for Insurance
Managed packages are the first packages you install in your Insurance install or upgrade process.

To make it easier to configure Insurance after installing or upgrading, install the unmanaged package that contains the Installation Assistant.
title: Installing and Upgrading Salesforce Insurance
